  "title": "Pharmacist (NUHS@Home)*(5612)",
  "description": "<p>As part of the multi-disciplinary team with the National University Health System (NUHS)@Home, you will provide quality pharmaceutical care as our <strong>Pharmacist</strong>.</p>\n<p><strong>Job Responsibilities</strong></p>\n<p>* Review transfer medications appropriately, contact patients pre-transfer on medication supply needed, and answer medicine related questions</p>\n<p>* Medication counselling on transfer medications by a variety of means (in-person and virtual)</p>\n<p>* Medication reconciliation</p>\n<p>* Review discharge prescriptions appropriately</p>\n<p>* Verify new orders by the physicians and identify inappropriate medication/doses if relevant</p>\n<p>* Assist with perform medication supply duty</p>\n<p>* Follow up on medication preparation status</p>\n<p>* Undertake duties which may be assigned by the NUHS staff member depending on the requirements</p>\n<p><strong>Requirements</strong></p>\n<p>* Bachelor of Science in Pharmacy from an accredited college by Singapore Pharmacy Council</p>\n<p>* At least 2 years of relevant experience</p>\n<p>* Fully registered with the Singapore Pharmacy Council</p>\n<p>* Possess excellent communication, interpersonal and organisation skills</p>\n<p>* Able to work independently and in a team</p>\n<p>* Undertake duties which may be assigned by the NUHS staff member depending on the requirement</p>\n<p>* Weekdays and/or weekends working hours are available</p>",
